### Airline Booking System API Tests
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tool

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@flightId = 
@routeId = 
@scheduleId = 
@aircraftId = 

### Get Welcome Message
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Get All Flights
GET {{baseUrl}}/flights

### Search Flights
GET {{baseUrl}}/flights/search?origin=JFK&destination=LAX&departureDate=2024-12-25&passengers=2&page=1&limit=10

### Get Flight by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/flights/{{flightId}}

### Get Flights by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/flights/status/scheduled

### Get Flights by Date
GET {{baseUrl}}/flights/date/2024-12-25

### Create Flight
POST {{baseUrl}}/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightNumber": "AA123",
  "routeId": "{{routeId}}",
  "scheduleId": "{{scheduleId}}",
  "aircraftId": "{{aircraftId}}",
  "departureDate": "2024-12-25",
  "gate": "A12",
  "terminal": "1",
  "status": "scheduled"
}

### Update Flight
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/flights/{{flightId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "gate": "B15",
  "terminal": "2",
  "status": "boarding",
  "availableSeats": 150,
  "bookedSeats": 50
}

### Update Flight Status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/flights/{{flightId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "delayed"
}

### Delete Flight
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/flights/{{flightId}}

